SALMONELLA MELEAGRIDIS, UPDATE - CANADA
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Salmonella meleagridis, international surveillance 971007001618
Salmonella meleangridis: RFI 970926232732
Date: Sat, 18 Oct 1997 11:48:24 -0400
From: "Robert A. LaBudde" <ral@lcfltd.com>
Source: FSNET (D. Powell, Univ. Guelph)& Health Canada, LCDC

Alberta Health LCDC has been informed of 13 additional cases of
salmonellosis that have been attributed to _S. meleagridis_ between August
and October. Eight are residents of Northern Alberta, the ninth is a
resident in Northwest Territories. There have also been 3 laboratory
confirmed cases reported from British Columbia, and 1 from Quebec. The
case tally for 1997 is now 47: 22 from Alberta; 18 from Ontario; 3 from
BC; 1 each from Manitoba, Saskatchewan, Quebec and Northwest Territories.
The Division of Disease Surveillance, LCDC, would appreciate being notified
of any similar cases.
--
Robert A. LaBudde, PhD, PAS, Dpl. ACAFS
e-mail: ral@lcfltd.com
